  "prompt": "Where is the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near or on University of Washington campus?",
  "response": "To find the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near or on the University of Washington campus, consider the following options:\n\n1. **University Bookstore**: This is a convenient option on campus; they may have a selection of vitamins and supplements at competitive prices.\n\n2. **Local Pharmacies**: Stores like Walgreens and CVS often have competitive prices on vitamins. Check their websites or apps for any current promotions or discounts.\n\n3. **Grocery Stores**: Nearby grocery stores like Safeway, QFC, or Trader Joe's often stock vitamins and may offer sales.\n\n4. **Health Food Stores**: Places like Whole Foods or smaller health food stores might have a variety of vitamin B-12 options, sometimes at reasonable prices, especially their store brands.\n\n5. **Online Retailers**: If you\u2019re okay with waiting for delivery, websites like Amazon often have competitive pricing for vitamins, and you can read reviews before purchasing.\n\nIt\u2019s a good idea to call ahead or check online for availability and prices, as they can vary. Additionally, consider looking for student discounts or loyalty programs at local stores.",
